longBusinessSummary: GC International, Inc. manufactures metal products primarily for inclusion in products sold by electronics, computer, and aerospace companies. It also manufactures its products for the production of audio recording master discs. It operates in two divisions, A. L. Johnson and Apollo Masters. The A. L. Johnson Division produces thin-walled aluminum castings, which are used in medical, electronics, computer housings, and camera parts. The Apollo Masters division processes polished aluminum substrates. This segment's products are sold to audio recording engineers. GC International was co-founded by F. Willard Griffith II and Richard R. Carlson in 1975. The company is based in Atherton, California.
